The Woodwards.

The king's demesnes, it must be reinembered, formed but a portion of the lands within his forests. The residue included extensive woods, over which the owners enjoyed most of the ordinary rights of property. In fact, the only limitation upon their rights may be expressed briefiy by saying that they could do nothing by which the woods would cease to afford shelter for the beasts 01 1110 forest.
